<p>I am trying to code a perl program to compare the "parts of speech" tags of two text files and print the matched tags along with the corresponding words in a separate file in Windows. </p>  <pre><code>File1: boy N went V loves V girl N File2: boy N swims V girl N loves V </code></pre>  <p>The expected output:     boy N N     girl N N     loves V V</p>  <p>The columns are separated by tabs. The coding I did so far:</p>  <pre><code>use strict; use warnings;  my $filename = 'file1.txt'; open(my $fh, $filename)   or die "Could not open file '$filename'";  while (my $row = &lt;$fh&gt;) {   chomp $row;   print "$row\n"; } my $tagfile = 'file2.txt'; open(my $tg, $tagfile)   or die "Could not open file '$filename'"; while (my $row = &lt;$tg&gt;) {     chomp $row;     print "$row\n";     }  </code></pre>